subSubSection.paragraph:
Type horizon: Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) Marília Formation of the Bauru Group (
Dias-Brito et al ., 2001
).

Although the surface of some parts of this specimen is broken, there are no perceptible taphonomic deformations. The preservation of DGM 1480- R is the same as observed in other dinosaur bones collected in this area, also including other crocodylomorphs (e.g. Campos & Kellner, 1999 ; Kellner & Campos, 2000 ;
Carvalho et al ., 2004
).
